				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The movie &#8217;21&#8242;, about the MIT Blackjack Team opens next Friday, March 28.  From the preview press, it sounds like this may be a cinematic <a href="http://www.cs.virginia.edu/~evans/cs551/manifests/1011.html">breakthrough of Gaussian proportions</a>!</p>
<p>MIT&#8217;s student newspaper has an interview with Ben Mezrich (author of <em>Bringing Down the House</em> on which the movie is based) and Jeffrey Ma (on whom one of the characters in the film is based):<br />
<a href="http://www-tech.mit.edu/V128/N12/blackjack.html"><em>MIT, Vegas, Hollywood</em></a>, The Tech, March 14, 2008.</p>
<p>
Sony&#8217;s official movie site: <a href="http://www.sonypictures.com/movies/21/"><em>http://www.sonypictures.com/movies/21/</em></a>.</p>
